03:43.493 --> 03:45.370
Marked by my lipstick.

03:45.537 --> 03:48.166
Mikey, kiss it, good luck.

03:48.416 --> 03:50.377
- There we go.
- Oh, he licked it. Bless him.

03:50.586 --> 03:52.463
Don't eat it. We're gonna need it.

03:53.131 --> 03:56.301
This is Burkittsville,
formerly Blair.

03:56.802 --> 03:59.764
A small quiet Maryland town.

04:00.307 --> 04:02.852
Like a small, quiet town anywhere.

04:03.060 --> 04:07.608
Some 20 families laid roots here
over 200 years ago.

04:08.317 --> 04:11.279
Many remain, either on this hill...

04:11.738 --> 04:13.616
...or in the town below.

04:14.909 --> 04:18.414
An unusually high number of
children are buried here...

04:18.831 --> 04:21.125
...most of whom passed
in the 1940's.

04:21.918 --> 04:26.090
Yet no one here recalls anything
unusual about this time,...

04:26.424 --> 04:28.218
...not to us, anyway.

04:28.552 --> 04:30.513
Yet legend tells
A different story,...

04:30.763 --> 04:33.058
...whose evidence is all around us.

04:33.767 --> 04:35.394
Etched in stone.

04:42.195 --> 04:45.783
We have shot the first scene,
the cemetery scene.

04:45.950 --> 04:47.827
The opening is shot.

04:48.203 --> 04:51.791
We're doing a documentary
about the Blair Witch.

04:52.834 --> 04:56.756
- Have you heard of the Witch?
- That's an old, old story.

04:57.048 --> 04:58.132
As I remember,...

04:58.341 --> 05:01.428
...Mr. Parr was an old hermit,...

05:02.221 --> 05:05.642
...and he lived up on a mountain.
He'd been there,...

05:05.809 --> 05:07.186
...for a long, long, time.

05:07.353 --> 05:09.564
- You heard of the Blair Witch?
- Several times.

05:09.814 --> 05:12.026
What was the first incident?

05:12.193 --> 05:15.864
I've heard stories about it
from people and neighbors,

05:16.073 --> 05:19.243
I also saw a documentary on the
television...

05:19.494 --> 05:22.748
...about her and legends
of Maryland,...

05:22.915 --> 05:26.586
...my grandmother told us the story
to make us go to bed early.

05:26.753 --> 05:30.175
They say if you stay up after dark
or walk around the house...

05:30.341 --> 05:31.885
...the Blair witch will get you.

05:32.094 --> 05:36.391
In the fall or winter of 1940,...

05:36.600 --> 05:39.687
...some young kids
started disappearing.

05:39.979 --> 05:41.606
Nobody knew...

05:42.315 --> 05:44.527
...why they were disappearing.

05:46.863 --> 05:49.950
- A kind of an omen, isn't it?
- The creepiest story about her...

05:50.618 --> 05:52.913
...was that two men out hunting...

05:53.038 --> 05:56.709
...camped near the cabin
she's supposed to haunt...

05:56.960 --> 05:57.627
No. No.

05:57.752 --> 06:00.047
...and they just disappeared
forever.

06:00.798 --> 06:03.802
I'm just telling a scary story,
but it's not true.

06:04.011 --> 06:04.845
It's not true.

06:05.012 --> 06:08.350
One day, old Mr. Parr
came into the market...

06:08.600 --> 06:10.811
...and said "I'm finally finished".

06:10.978 --> 06:11.979
And what did he mean by that?

06:12.188 --> 06:13.815
Nobody knew at first...

06:14.024 --> 06:15.985
But the police finally...

06:16.151 --> 06:17.737
went up the mountain...

06:18.488 --> 06:22.702
...and found the bodies of seven
kids in his house.

06:23.161 --> 06:26.498
He would take the kids down
to the basement in twos...

06:26.665 --> 06:28.960
...and he'd make one
face the corner...

06:29.961 --> 06:31.755
...and he'd kill the other one...

06:32.256 --> 06:35.343
...then he'd kill the one in
the corner too.

06:35.802 --> 06:37.304
Those were the seven kids
that were missing

06:37.471 --> 06:40.475
They brought the kids out of
the woods one at a time...

06:40.642 --> 06:43.896
...it was terrible, it upset
the whole community.

06:44.105 --> 06:45.982
He said he couldn't take
the eyes watching him...

06:46.233 --> 06:50.071
...that's why he made them
face the corner like that.

06:50.238 --> 06:52.115
All my life I've believed...

06:52.282 --> 06:54.994
...in witches and ghosts and
that kind of stuff

06:55.119 --> 06:56.997
Do you believe there are some
in this area?

06:57.205 --> 06:57.873
Oh, definitely.

06:58.081 --> 07:00.042
- Do you believe in witchcraft?
- No.

07:01.002 --> 07:03.213
- Are you religious?
- Yep.

07:03.422 --> 07:04.340
Alrighty.

07:04.507 --> 07:08.679
Creepy stuff, but I think
something's happening with her.

07:08.846 --> 07:11.224
And do you think she could
still be up there now?

07:11.474 --> 07:13.185
- I don't go up there.
- You don't?

07:13.352 --> 07:14.728
I believe enough not to go.

07:14.853 --> 07:18.275
They say the woods are haunted
and stuff like that.

07:18.525 --> 07:20.236
What? How are they haunted?

07:20.361 --> 07:24.533
Well there's not many people
who say that it's haunted...

07:24.700 --> 07:27.078
...but there was this old woman,
Mary Brown, who...

07:27.286 --> 07:28.288
Mary Brown?

07:28.455 --> 07:30.582
Yeah, and she was kind of crazy.

07:30.791 --> 07:32.669
How was she seen by the community?

07:32.919 --> 07:33.503
Crazy.

07:33.837 --> 07:37.759
There's the American flag,
it's Mary's house.

07:38.510 --> 07:39.594
I'm gonna bring her out.

07:39.803 --> 07:41.931
You look for the best light, okay?

07:42.139 --> 07:42.723
Okay.

07:45.560 --> 07:48.105
This is Mary's gate.

07:49.482 --> 07:51.860
I'm not even sure how to open it.

07:53.029 --> 07:55.949
And something interesting
happened to you once...

07:56.116 --> 07:58.244
You met the Blair witch?

07:59.120 --> 07:59.871
Yes.

08:00.038 --> 08:01.289
That is really...

08:01.623 --> 08:04.001
...kind of a scary story.

08:05.003 --> 08:06.338
To make ends meet...

08:06.505 --> 08:08.132
...my Dad and I

08:08.382 --> 08:10.593
...used to fish at Tappy's Creek.

08:10.927 --> 08:13.806
In Burkittsville.

08:14.432 --> 08:17.227
I was laying on the leaves...

08:17.936 --> 08:20.940
...watching my pole, and
looking at the sky...

08:21.357 --> 08:25.404
...and suddenly I felt
something near me...

08:25.905 --> 08:27.699
...an eerie feeling...

08:28.450 --> 08:30.411
...It was a woman...

08:30.995 --> 08:33.289
...only on her
arms and hands...

08:33.457 --> 08:35.333
...and everything...

08:35.543 --> 08:37.086
...she had hair...

08:37.796 --> 08:40.174
...dark, almost black hair...

08:40.841 --> 08:42.342
...like a horse...

08:42.594 --> 08:44.972
...like a fur, horse fur.

08:45.264 --> 08:46.515
Then on her arm...

08:46.933 --> 08:48.643
...she had a shawl...

08:49.436 --> 08:51.480
And she scared you,
or threatened you?

08:52.315 --> 08:55.736
She didn't say anything,
she just stared...

08:55.944 --> 08:57.822
...and then she opened her shawl...

08:58.156 --> 08:59.616
What was under there?

08:59.783 --> 09:02.787
She had hair on her
body like a horse.

09:02.995 --> 09:04.247
Hairy from head to toe?

09:04.456 --> 09:06.834
Yeah. And her legs...

09:07.167 --> 09:10.171
- How about her face?
- You could see she was a female.

09:10.881 --> 09:13.259
She was just strange looking.

09:14.010 --> 09:16.471
Thank God she's
not in the film business.

09:16.680 --> 09:19.851
She thinks she is.
She also says she's a ballerina.

09:20.143 --> 09:21.144
Get out.

09:21.353 --> 09:23.147
And she says she's a historian...

09:23.314 --> 09:24.148
I heard that.

09:24.315 --> 09:26.610
...and that she's a scientist
at the Department of Energy.

09:26.818 --> 09:29.989
I fucked up on Mary
with the depth of field.

09:30.198 --> 09:32.951
You measured it in meters?
We're not in Europe.

09:33.535 --> 09:35.580
The fucking lens
has meters on it.

09:35.830 --> 09:38.208
It also has our system.

09:39.168 --> 09:41.713
Nah, it has meters. Look.

09:43.799 --> 09:45.676
But it's an American camera.

09:45.885 --> 09:47.220
All those are meters.

09:47.596 --> 09:49.223
What about the brown ones?

09:49.390 --> 09:50.474
They're feet.

09:50.641 --> 09:52.435
The brown ones are on there, right?

09:52.644 --> 09:55.272
Yeah, but the white
ones are obvious.

09:55.397 --> 09:59.236
- Didn't you use this camera before?
- Yeah. Once before.

09:59.611 --> 10:01.405
How was today, guys?

10:02.699 --> 10:04.326
I learned a lot, man.

10:04.493 --> 10:06.287
About Mary Brown?

10:06.662 --> 10:09.124
No, I learned a lot about...

10:09.875 --> 10:10.959
16 mill?

10:11.377 --> 10:13.922
...about shooting, just
shooting documentaries.

10:15.132 --> 10:17.009
- We kicked some ass today.
- Cheers.

10:17.385 --> 10:18.553
Very good day.

10:18.761 --> 10:19.429
Excellent day.

10:19.638 --> 10:20.889
Very good first day.

10:21.098 --> 10:24.602
Let's do an equipment check,
after I call my mom.

10:24.811 --> 10:27.898
- I got a bag of Utz and a beer.
- We don't need that on film.

10:28.232 --> 10:30.026
So I guess you're covered then.

10:30.235 --> 10:33.823
Could you run it a little
to check it's okay?

10:34.365 --> 10:35.200
Sure.

10:35.575 --> 10:39.247
I just want to check it's loaded
properly so we can shoot...

10:40.582 --> 10:43.294
Okay, that's good, that's good.

10:43.586 --> 10:45.630
That's good, thank you.

10:46.423 --> 10:48.884
Let's relax, because we've got
a long day tomorrow.

10:49.135 --> 10:51.346
Today's been easy.

10:51.554 --> 10:54.183
We're gonna have to do a lot
of hiking, carry a lot of weight.

10:54.391 --> 10:55.810
We're preparing.

10:55.977 --> 10:59.231
Shut up, smartass.
Pour me a shot, please.

10:59.481 --> 11:03.070
- I'm freaking out.
- You can't, you're the director.

11:03.278 --> 11:07.116
I fucking have to do this now,
okay? Do we have any weed?

11:08.410 --> 11:09.578
Here I go.

11:10.371 --> 11:12.081
Drink! Drink!

11:14.918 --> 11:16.879
